reviews.review:
By far the worst Star Wars movie ever made. I initially liked this new trilogy too. Force Awakens was great and even though I was in the minority I liked The Last Jedi. This film has horrible pacing and has the worst explanations for all of the questions in Force Awakens. This is lazy writing at its best and It's more of a sequel to a Force Awakens than Last Jedi. 

What bothered me the most is this doesn't feel like Star Wars. It feels cheap and extremely rushed. The ending is ridiculously stupid and this film is filled with so much member berries that makes you think "what?!?!? why? This makes no sense."

I don't recommend this movie and if this is the end of the Skywalker saga, which this sequel trilogy didn't really have much to do with the Skywalker's, then it's a very disappointing ending. It's so bad I don't recommend the sequel trilogy at all. Skip it and pretend it didn't happen.
As a Star Wars fan, this movie was great.

An intense heart pounding adventure that grabs ahold of you from the opening minutes, and doesn't let go for over two hours. It's step on the gas and go adventure, with less exposition than either of the previous two films. It's fun, answers many questions about the series and created a few "final moments" that are simply breathtaking. A movie for fans first, and obviously critics second, it will stand out for years to come.

I remember the impact of seeing the 1st Star Wars in 1977. Some in the middle of the series were a let down. Last few have been much better. This was very very good and among the best. Big ending to 42 year old series. See it.

Going into this movie I was bracing for disappointment-- brought on by my own post-Last Jedi skepticism, so I was delighted at how well it turned out. The Rise of Skywalker managed to preserve and strengthen the only story line I was interested in from TLJ, and did manage to fix some of the damage episode 8 left. There were some clunky moments from the ensemble, but it was mostly a script issue rather than an actor issue. All is forgiven though by the preservation of the overall story arch and original Star Wars themes. I was left wanting more, but that is because there are some great characters that I have really come to love, and I wish there was more.
A little long, could of used one less fight scene. it was a good ending to a 42 year battle of good vs evil. A lot of subtle references and salutes to episodes 4,5,6.
Awesome, great way to end the saga.

To be fair, I am in my 40s and probably will be considered as old school by younger viewers. Just can not help to think Star Wars is just not as cool as it used to be. I actually love the Disney princess movies when I am in the mood for it, just sad to see Star Wars is been turned into one. Too cheesy compare to what Star Wars used to be.
Loved it! Wonderful finish to the story.
Makes me wish JJ Abrams would have just done all 3 movies.
